
[1]retention

   RETEN'TION, n. [L. retentio, retineo; re and teneo, to hold.]

   1. The act of retaining or keeping.

   2. The power of retaining; the faculty of the mind by which it retains
   ideas.

   3. In medicine, the power of retaining, or that state of contraction in
   the solid or vascular parts of the body, by which they hold their
   proper contents and prevent in voluntary evacuations; undue retention
   of some natural discharge.

   4. The act of withholding; restraint.

   5. Custody; confinement. [Not in use.]
